text:
I have the pattern. Line 39 of `trustmanager_types.go` shows the exact syntax. Here's the complete implementation:

---

## File to modify

**`api/operator/v1alpha1/certmanager_types.go`** — Add the CEL validation marker to the `CertManager` type, right before the type declaration (alongside the other kubebuilder markers):

```diff
 // +genclient
 // +genclient:nonNamespaced
 // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object
 //+kubebuilder:object:root=true
 //+kubebuilder:subresource:status
 //+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Cluster
+// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule="self.metadata.name == 'cluster'",message="CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'"

 // CertManager is the Schema for the certmanagers API
 // +operator-sdk:csv:customresourcedefinitions:displayName="CertManager"
 type CertManager struct {
```

The marker is added on a new line between `//+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Cluster` and the blank line before the `// CertManager is the Schema...` comment.

## Exact edit

In `certmanager_types.go`, the current lines 180–189:

```go
// +genclient
// +genclient:nonNamespaced
// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object
//+kubebuilder:object:root=true
//+kubebuilder:subresource:status
//+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Cluster

// CertManager is the Schema for the certmanagers API
// +operator-sdk:csv:customresourcedefinitions:displayName="CertManager"
type CertManager struct {
```

Replace with:

```go
// +genclient
// +genclient:nonNamespaced
// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object
//+kubebuilder:object:root=true
//+kubebuilder:subresource:status
//+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Cluster
// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule="self.metadata.name == 'cluster'",message="CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'"

// CertManager is the Schema for the certmanagers API
// +operator-sdk:csv:customresourcedefinitions:displayName="CertManager"
type CertManager struct {
```

## Commands to run

After making the edit, run from the repository root:

```bash
cd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-baseline
make manifests
```

This single command regenerates both:
1. The CRD YAML in `config/crd/bases/` — it will add an `x-kubernetes-validations` block at the top level of the CertManager CRD schema with the CEL rule.
2. The bundle manifest in `bundle/manifests/` — it will pick up the updated CRD.

## What the generated CRD change looks like

In the generated CRD (e.g. `config/crd/bases/operator.openshift.io_certmanagers.yaml`), the `openAPIV3Schema` for `CertManager` will gain:

```yaml
x-kubernetes-validations:
  - message: CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'
    rule: self.metadata.name == 'cluster'
```

This ensures that any `CertManager` object is rejected at admission time unless its `metadata.name` is exactly `cluster`, making it a singleton — matching the same pattern used by `TrustManager`.
